---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Political Parties Database">
  <article class="prose page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">blah blah blah ai slop alarm</p>
    <h1>About the database</h1>

    <h2>Scope</h2>
    <p>
      The database is intended to describe active, inactive and historical political parties,
      electoral coalitions and comparable political organisations. Each entry is stored as
      structured data and rendered through one shared page template.
    </p>

    <h2>Source policy</h2>
    <p>
      Dates, leadership, status and affiliations should be linked to explicit sources.
      Ideological labels and left–right placement should preferably rely on independent
      secondary sources rather than self-description alone. Uncertain claims should be
      marked as uncertain instead of being inferred.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial workflow</h2>
    <p>
      Every entry has a last-reviewed date, a completeness level and an optional review flag.
      The site build validates the data schema. Invalid URLs, malformed identifiers and
      missing required fields stop deployment instead of silently producing broken pages.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
